@page "/guides"

<MudGrid>
    <MudItem xs="12">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h2" Align="Align.Center">Guides</MudText>
        <MudDivider Class="mb-2" />
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            I have written a few guides on various topics. Some guides will be related to nuget packages I have created.
            Others
            will be about things/topics/solutions that I have found to be useful and think others will too.
        </MudText>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Align="Align.Left">Nuget guides</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            These are guides I have written about the nuget packages I have made. They don't only focus on the nuget
            themselves but
            also the surrounding technologies, i.e. a guide about NameBasedAuthorizeViewComponent nuget will explain how
            to use it but
            also walk through the process of getting Authentication working in Blazor. NameBasedAuthorizeViewComponent
            relies on
            Authentication.
        </MudText>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" Class="mud-width-full">
        <MudCard Elevation="4" Class="gc">
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Blazor Authentication & Authorization with Okta and
                    NameBasedAuthorizeViewComponent</MudText>
                <MudDivider DividerType="DividerType.Middle" Class="my-6" />
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    A guide to setting up Authentication & Authorization in blazor using Okta as
                    an Identity Provider and setting up the NameBasedAuthorizeViewComponent nuget.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
            <MudCardActions Style="flex-direction: row-reverse;">
                <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Link="NameBasedAuthorizeView">Read Guide
                </MudButton>
                <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary"
                    Link="https://github.com/ZieMcd/NameBasedAuthenticationComponent" Target="_blank">GitHud</MudButton>
            </MudCardActions>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" Class="mud-width-full">
        <MudCard Elevation="4">
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Using Hashicorp vault as custom configuration provider in asp.net projects with
                    HashiCorpAsConfiguration</MudText>
                <MudDivider DividerType="DividerType.Middle" Class="my-6" />
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    A guide to set up an instance of Hashicorp vault to store secrets and using HashiCorpAsConfiguration
                    nuget to access them in your asp.net project as Configuration.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
            <MudCardActions Style="flex-direction: row-reverse;">
                <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Link="HashiCorpAsConfiguration">Read Guide
                </MudButton>
                <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary"
                    Link="https://github.com/ZieMcd/HashiCorpVaultAsConfiguration" Target="_blank">GitHud</MudButton>
            </MudCardActions>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Align="Align.Left">Other guides</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            Some other guides about things I think are worth a share.
        </MudText>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" Class="mud-width-full">
        <MudCard Elevation="4">
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Using Kubernetes Cron Jobs and Dotnet worker services to scheduled background
                    tasks</MudText>
                <MudDivider DividerType="DividerType.Middle" Class="my-6" />
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Use Kubernetes Cron Jobs to Start up and shut down instances of dotnet worker
                    services
                    to scheduled background tasks.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
            <MudCardActions Style="flex-direction: row-reverse;">
                <MudButton Variant="Variant.Text" Color="Color.Primary" Link="KubernetesCronJobs">Read Guide</MudButton>
            </MudCardActions>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>
</MudGrid>

